  <body>

  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_clinical_intervention">CLINICAL INTERVENTION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>
 is used to treat conditions such as cancer, thyroid disorders and some blood disorders.  </p>
  <p>
During cancer 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>
, controlled doses of high-energy radiation, usually X-rays, destroy cancer 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_cell">CELLS</xref>
 in the affected area.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>
, see the 
    <xref href="https://www.cancer.gov/dictionary?CdrID=44295"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National Cancer Institute website</xref>
.  </p>

